HEADWORD: Phloretin
<hw>Phlor"e*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
Phlorizin.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A bitter white crystalline
substance obtained by the decomposition of phlorizin, and formerly used
to some extent as a substitute for quinine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

